
[1]affeer

   AFFEE'R, v.t. To confirm. [Not used.]

   AFFEE'R, v.t.

   In law, to assess or reduce an arbitrary penalty or amercement to a
   precise sum; to reduce a general amercement to a sum certain, according
   to the circumstances of the case.
